KATSINA – Senator Ahmed Babba-Kaita has on Tuesday been declared winner of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) candidate for Katsina North Senatorial District (Daura Zone). Alhaji Aminu Bello, the Chairman PDP electoral committee for Katsina State announced this shortly after the party delegates cast their votes in the primary election held at the state Secretariat. “Sen. Babba-Kaita is the only aspirant that the party sold nomination forms to unopposed across the country”. -Advertisement- He noted that, as a result of the support given by party delegates in the 12 LGAs, the party hereby declared him winner of the primary election. Speaking with newsmen, Babba-Kaita expressed gratitude to God for giving him the opportunity as well as the delegates who found him worthy to contest. According to him, “since decamping to the party, I have received tremendous support and hospitality from all and sundry.” Babba-Kaita further assured that, he will continue to facilitate more numerous developmental projects if re-elected in 2023. He prayed for the success of the party in all the political seats, for the country to continue benefiting from good leadership of the party. POLL “I am using this opportunity to call on aspirants who won their primary election and those who lost, to remain vigilant, patience and persevere to enable the party succeed.” “And they should also give all the needed support for the emergence of the party in 2023″, the Senator charged party members.” In his remark, Alhaji Salisu Majigiri, one of the PDP gubernatorial candidate called on the electorates to elect aspirants based on merit and credibility come 2023. Majigiri also appealed to the populace to elect credible and intelligent leaders, especially the candidates brought by the party.